Courtesy of #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - The government is calling on Nelson Mandela Bay Metro residents to protect water sources. READ: SA's water crisis | NMB keeps Day Zero at bay The metro has so far managed to stave off Day Zero but it may not be for much longer if resources continue to be polluted. Meanwhile, Nelson Mandela Bay mayor, Eugene Johnson has led a public water awareness campaign in Gqeberha. She and a team from the municipality went out in the early hours of the morning targeting major traffic intersections, and spreading the word about saving water.  eNCA's Nceba Ntlanganiso has the details. #eNCA #DStv403